				<div class="section">
					<h3>
						Portal Settings
						<a name="Portal_Settings"></a>
					</h3>
					<p>The Portal Settings can be found in the
						SetupGlobalConfigOverride process, that sets the portal config
						object. The process also sets the content and formatting language
						to swedish by default, regardless of the language of the user.
						Please note that these portal settings can not be changed in the
						Administration UI, it's part of the portal project. If there is a
						change, than a Redeployment is necesary. Usually these settings
						are changed one time, at the beginning of the project.</p>
					<table border="1" class="table table-striped">
						<tbody>
							<tr class="a">
								<th align="left">Configuration</th>
								<th align="left">Setting</th>
							</tr>
							<tr class="b">
								<td align="left">Show Header Banner</td>
								<td align="left">Header Banner is shown, but no E.ON Logo</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class="a">
								<td align="left">Show Welcome Page</td>
								<td align="left">Yes, the Welcome Page Override dialog is displayed
								</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class="b">
								<td align="left">Show Process Start List</td>
								<td align="left">No (only Developer role see the start list</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class="a">
								<td align="left">Book Task Button</td>
								<td align="left">Book Button is not present in toolbar when you open
									a task</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class="b">
								<td align="left">Max Tab Count</td>
								<td align="left">6, Sets the number of parallel open tabs in the
									portal</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class="a">
								<td align="left">Running Task List</td>
								<td align="left">Not all columns are displayed. Details see config
									process</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class="b">
								<td align="left">Finished Case List</td>
								<td align="left">Not all columns are displayed. Details see config
									process</td>
							</tr>
						</tbody>
					</table>
				</div>
			</div>
